  <title>Introduction to Endless</title>

  <p>Endless has been created just for you. When you first turn your computer on,
  you'll find some important applications already installed on your desktop, and
  a taskbar at the very bottom of your screen.</p>

  <p>The taskbar provides access to important things like your windows and
  applications, your calendar and clock, and system properties like sound and
  networking. There, you can change the volume, edit your Wi-Fi
  connection details, check your battery status, log out or switch users, and
  turn off your computer. We have also included the possibility to connect to
  Facebook on this taskbar, so that you can keep in touch with your friends
  more easily than ever!</p>

<links type="section"/>

<section id="activities">
  <title><app>App Store</app> overview</title>

  <p>Your computer should be incredibly useful to you both online and offline.
  For that reason, we have packed Endless with all sorts of applications and
  content for you to explore and discover. You can add more apps to your desktop
  by clicking on <media its:translate="no" type="image" mime="image/png"
  src="figures/eos-icon-more-apps.png"> the plus</media> button from the desktop.
  This will launch our <app>App Store</app>, which is full of free applications
  for you to install on your desktop.</p>

  <p>The <app>App Store</app> is divided into three sections: <gui>Apps</gui>,
  <gui>Websites</gui>, and <gui>Folders</gui>. You can browse applications you
  may want to install by category, add shortcuts to your favorite websites onto
  your desktop, or simply create new folders to organize all of your things in a
  way that makes sense to you.</p>


