<section id="lockscreen">
  <title>Lock Screen</title>

  <p>When you lock your screen, or it locks automatically, the lock screen is
  displayed. In addition to protecting your desktop while you're away from your
  computer, the lock screen displays the date and time. It also shows
  information about your battery and network status, and allows you to control
  media playback.</p>

  <list style="compact">
    <item>
      <p><link xref="privacy-screen-lock">Learn more about the lock
      screen.</link></p>
    </item>
  </list>

</section>

<section id="window-list">
  <title>Hot Corner</title>

    <p>Endless allows you to see all of your open windows and tasks so that you
    can multitask like a pro. To access this cool feature, move your mouse
    pointer to the very bottom right-hand corner of your screen. You can then
    click on the window or task that you'd like to open, so that you can get
    around much, much faster. For example, if you want to return to the desktop
    from layers of open applications and media, just click on an open space
    behind your open windows!</p>
